org.jtimer.Annotations

Annotation Type Warmup


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface Warmup
    Used to specify an amount of non-timed repetitions for the methods so that the CPU can warm up. I'm not really sure if this has any tangible benefit, although I will test it out. iterations() Has an iterations count, by default this is 10 although it can be changed if you want.
    Author:
    MagneticZero
